definition.value: A 2-demethylmenaquinol having a side chain composed of six isoprenoid units.
A xi-progoitrin(1-) that is the conjugate base of progoitrin.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of dTDP-3,4-didehydro-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucose; major species at pH 7.3.
A menaquinol having a side chain composed of nine isoprenoid units.
A 2-demethylmenaquinol having a side chain composed of nine isoprenoid units.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and linoleoyl respectively.
A menaquinol whose structure comprises a 2-methylbenzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of ten isoprenoid units.
A 2-demethylmenaquinol whose structure comprises a benzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of ten isoprenoid units.
A menaquinol whose structure comprises a 2-methylbenzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of eleven isoprenoid units.
A 2-demethylmenaquinol whose structure comprises a benzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of eleven isoprenoid units.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl groups specified at position 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

A biguanide compound which has isopropyl and p-chlorophenyl substituents on the terminal N atoms. A prophylactic antimalarial drug, it works by inhibiting the enzyme dihydrofolate reductase, which is involved in the reproduction of the malaria parasites Plasmodium falciparum and P. vivax within the red blood cells.
A menaquinol whose structure comprises a 2-methylbenzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of twelve isoprenoid units.
A 2-demethylmenaquinol whose structure comprises a benzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of twelve isoprenoid units.
A menaquinol whose structure comprises a 2-methylbenzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of thirteen isoprenoid units.
A 2-demethylmenaquinol whose structure comprises a benzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of thirteen isoprenoid units.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3,5-dihydroxyphenylacetyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A  1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and linoleoyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl) respectively.
The organic disodium salt of 4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl 3-aminopropyl phosphate
A 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl  and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.

The organophosphate oxoanion formed by proton loss from each of the phospho groups of dihydrogen 4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl 3-aminopropyl phosphate
A member of the class of dinitroanisoles that is 2-nitroanisole in which the hydrogen para to the methoxy group is replaced by a second nitro group.
An amino sugar phosphate that is 4-O-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminylphospho)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine linked glycosidically to a (3-aminopropoxy)(hydroxy)phosphoryl group.
A phenolate anion obtained from 2,4-dinitrophenol. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and (9Z)-hexadecenoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 38:6 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl respectively.
The organic trisodium salt of 4-O-[4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho]-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl 3-aminopropyl phosphate.
A phosphatidylcholine 40:4 in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the two acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively
A phosphatidylcholine 34:3 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoleoyl and linoleoyl respectively.

The organophosphate oxoanion formed by proton loss from each of the phospho groups of 4-O-[4-O-(2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosylphospho]-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucosyl 3-aminopropyl phosphate.

An amino sugar phosphate that is 4-O-[4-O-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminylphospho)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminylphospho]-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine linked glycosidically to a (3-aminopropoxy)(hydroxy)phosphoryl group.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoleoyl and stearoyl respectively.
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group of rifamycin SV. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group of 27-O-demethylrifamycin SV. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A  phosphatidylcholine 38:4  in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecanoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and (11Z,14Z)-eicosadienoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and (11Z)-eicosenoyl respectively.
A cholestenoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (25S)-3beta-hydroxy-5-cholesten-26-oic acid.
A  phosphatidylcholine 33:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoyl and (9Z)-heptadecenoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 30:1 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are myristoyl and palmitoleoyl respectively.

A dioxo monocarboxylic acid that consists of hydrindane bearing oxo and hydroxy substituents at positions 1 and 5 respectively as well as a 2-carboxyethyl substituent at position 4 (the 3aS,4S,5R,7aS diastereomer).
Any member of the class of nitroanisoles in which the anisole ring is substituted by two nitro groups.
A 1-monolysocardiolipin in which the remaining phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1, 2 and 2' are specified as linoleoyl.

A hydroxamic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the primary amino group of N-(3-aminopropyl)-N-hydroxyacetamide (2 mol eq.) with the carboxy groups at positions 1 and 3 of citric acid. It is a siderophore produced by Bacillus megaterium and Anabaena species.
A 2-monolysocardiolipinin which the remaining phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 1' are specified as linoleoyl while that at position 2' is  specified as oleoyl.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxodotriacontanoic acid (3-oxolacceroic acid).

A tricarboxylic acid that is citric acid in which the pro-R carboxy group has been esterified with the primary hydroxy group of 2-hydroxy-1-{(2S)-1-[(2-hydroxyethyl)amino]-1-oxopropan-2-yl}-5-oxoproline. It is a siderophore isolated from bacteria closely associated or symbiotic with toxic, bloom-forming dinoflagellates.
An organic heterotricyclic compound consisting of a furan ring ortho-fused to a quinoline.
